    "attributes": {
        "action": "Prohibit the use of cameras to monitor the activity of staff",
        "additional_details": "Where cameras are needed to ensure safety, these can be deployed in a way that ensures they do not monitor the activity of workers.",
        "background": "Employers should not be allowed to use cameras to monitor staff. This is an infringement of privacy, which is a basic human right. This is a particular issue for HGV drivers, who spend much of their time in the cab, often monitored by camera.",
